==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Steinkirk
<hw>Stein"kirk`</hw> <pr>(st⟦imac⟧n"-)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[So called from the battle of <ets>Steinkirk</ets>, in 1692, on
which occasion the French nobles had no time to arrange their lace
neckcloths.]</ety> <def>A kind of neckcloth worn in a loose and
disorderly fashion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steep</ent>⟦br⟧

